A2 (Fig. 
6A
). Allobasis without abexopodal seta. Exopod represented by minute bare seta. Endopod with 2 rows of inner spinules - 1 subapical and 1 proximal -; additionally, with 2 bare spines and 1 fine bare seta accompanied by 4 anterior spinules; apically with 5 setae, of which 3 geniculated and 1 biplumose.

Md (Fig. 
6B
) with slender gnathobase bearing 4 teeth; palp 1-segmented, with 5 setae (1 missing, and 1 damaged in Fig. 
6B
